	<div id="breadcrumbs" class="breadcrumbs"><ul class="wrapper"><li class="item-home"><a class="bread-link bread-home" href="http://www.chabe.fr/en" title="Accueil">Accueil</a></li><li class="separator-breadcrumbs separator-breadcrumbs-home"> <i class="sepa">/</i> </li><li class="item-cat"><a href="http://www.chabe.fr/en/category/sectors-en">Sectors</a></li><li class="separator-breadcrumbs"> <i class="sepa">/</i> </li><li class="item-cat"><a href="http://www.chabe.fr/en/category/sectors-en/tourism-en">Tourism</a></li><li class="separator-breadcrumbs"> <i class="sepa">/</i> </li><li class="item-current item-9387"><span class="bread-current bread-9387" title="Bordeaux on top of the most <br>attractive destinations in 2017">Bordeaux on top of the most <br>attractive destinations in 2017</span></li></ul></div>		

	<div class="wrapper">
	
	<div id="primary" class="content-area">

		<main id="main" class="site-main">
			
			
				<!-- section -->
				<section>

					
						
<!-- article -->
<article id="post-9387" class="post-9387 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-bordeaux-en category-tourism-en" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Article">


	<footer>
		
		<div class="date">

			<time  datetime="2017-02-15">February 2017</time>

			<!-- Go to www.addthis.com/dashboard to customize your tools -->
			<div class="addthis_sharing_toolbox alignright"></div>
	
		</div>

	</footer>
	
			
	<section class="post-text post-content" itemprop="text">	

		<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-9388" src="http://www.chabe.fr/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/miroir2a_10.jpg" alt="Miroir d'eau Bordeaux" width="550" height="367" srcset="http://www.chabe.fr/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/miroir2a_10.jpg 550w, http://www.chabe.fr/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/miroir2a_10-300x200.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px" /><span style="font-size: 12px;">Photo: Thomas Sanson &#8211; Mairie de Bordeaux</span></p>
<br><br>

Bordeaux begins this year attracting the attention of the world. Already voted <strong><a href="https://www.lonelyplanet.com/best-in-travel/cities">best city to visit</a></strong> by the Lonely Planet, it  has just been named  <strong><a href="http://www.latimes.com/travel/la-tr-17-places-2017-20170101-htmlstory.html" target="_blank">best destination for the year to come</a></strong> by the Los Angeles Times.

<br><br>

The reasons of this success? Bordeaux is appreciated for its<strong> gastronomy and its wine</strong>. Already famous worldwide for its wineyards, the city shines even more thanks to the opening of the Cité du Vin, a museum devoted to the history of wine that opened in 2016. The “sleeping beauty” is also admired for its<strong> architecture</strong> thanks to its many 18th century buildings. Finally, the<strong> dynamism </strong>of Bordeaux makes it attractive, in particular thanks to the new LGV line which connects the city with Europe’s high- speed train network and cuts travel time to Paris from three to two hours.

<br><br>

Our chauffeured car agency <a href="http://www.chabe.fr/en/agence/bordeaux">Chabé Bordeaux</a> rides this wave. The year 2016 was profitable thanks to the tourism, the wine and some cutting-edge industries and the year to come seems to be just as good with the<strong> opening of the LGV line</strong> which will surely increase weekend tourism, and <strong>Vinexpo</strong> in June (leading international wine and spirit event) for which Chabé, as for each edition, will drive clients, VIPs and business partners of the exhibitors.
	</section>

	
		<a class="btn-primary btn-newsletter clear" href="#" title="Receive our newsletter">Receive our newsletter</a>

			
	
</article>
